If you want the flavors to blend quickly just add all ingredients except the mayo & lemon to the shredded chicken and toss. Let it sit a few minutes then mix in the blended lemon/mayo. That way it only needs to rest about 30 minutes. Dried tarragon works fine too.

Rating: 4
Following previous reviewer's suggestions I poached the chicken (I used tenders) in chicken broth and added a couple sprigs of tarragon and a few lemon slices. I also finely chopped the chicken to help absorb the flavor of the mayo mixture. Lastly I served the salad on croissants for personal preference. My husband raved and it is just as good the next day (maybe with the addition of a bit more mayo). Definitely a keeper.

