Rating: 4
Delicious. I followed the recipe exactly except I used Greek yogurt with the mayo (1/2 and 1/2) to cut the calories, and I served on whole wheat wraps instead of rye bread. Mouth-watering, fresh, and super-tasty, and I loved the fresh tarragon with the lemon. And if you are not familiar with Greek yogurt - it is NOT like American yogurt. It's strained, so it is thicker, and it is not nearly as sweet as typical yogurt. It makes a fantastic substitute for sour cream, mayo, you name it. But with a nice reduction in the calories!

