Rating: 4
This salad was excellent. All the ingredients worked really well together. I did make some changes on the second go round; instead of celery I use fresh fennel or anise if you prefer. It complimented the tarragon very well. I didn't have a red onion so I used white and it worked out well, however it took away from the dishes color so to make up for it I added capers which turned out to be a really good choice. I would definitely recommend poaching the chicken in chicken broth instead of straight water. Me personally I also added a lemon peal, fresh tarragon, chopped green peppercorns, garlic, bay leaves and red pepper flakes to the broth. It gave it an extra kick. I also shredded the chicken (personal preference) and am thinking about adding pine nuts on the next go round.

